[0.008665, "o", "aegis-boot — Signed boot. Any ISO. Your keys.\r\n\r\naegis-boot is a USB rescue-stick builder with Secure Boot built-in.\r\nOther multi-ISO tools (Ventoy, YUMI) ask you to disable Secure Boot\r\nOR enroll their key into your firmware. aegis-boot reuses the same\r\nMicrosoft-signed shim → grub → kernel chain real distros use, so the\r\nstick boots on every laptop with default firmware out of the box.\r\n\r\nYou're 4 commands away from a working rescue stick:\r\n\r\n  1. aegis-boot doctor                check your host has the prereqs\r\n  2. aegis-boot init /dev/sdX         flash a fresh USB stick\r\n  3. aegis-boot fetch ubuntu-24.04   download a verified rescue ISO\r\n  4. aegis-boot add ubuntu.iso       copy the ISO onto the stick\r\n\r\nEach subcommand accepts --help for full usage and examples.\r\n\r\nTo learn the trust model:\r\n  - docs/HOW_IT_WORKS.md          5-minute conceptual walkthrough\r\n  - docs/TOUR.md                  step-by-step first-time guide\r\n  - docs/USB_LAYOUT.md            partition layout + signed-chain map\r\n\r\nTo see your laptop's compatibility:  aegis-boot compat --my-machine\r\nTo see what's on a stick:            aegis-boot list /dev/sdX\r\nTo audit past flashes:               aegis-boot attest list\r\n\r\nFor the full subcommand list:        aegis-boot --help\r\n"]
